Patients at the highest risk include the following:
Infants and children with chronic lung disease (bronchopulmonary dysplasia, cystic fibrosis) [16];
Preterm infants are less than 35 weeks gestational age [17];
Infants with congenital heart disease [18];
Infants exposed to second-hand smoke [19];
Immunocompromised patients (HIV) [20];
Infants with genetic disease (Down syndrome) [21].

