In Romania, 176 out of 1903 patients completed the program between September 2023 and March 2024, and the main barriers to immunoprophylaxis administration were as follows:
A total of 29%: Do not want to administrate the treatment anymore;
A total of 28%: HCP advice against the treatment;
A total of 18%: Difficult access to treatment;
A total of 15%: Family against the treatment;
A total of 10%: Others.
